<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-12-17T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-12-17T00:00:00-05:00" n="679" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d679">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 123.R27/66.</note>
                        <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-12-17">
                                    <hi rend="italic">December 17, 1912</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>The British Ambassador has in person conveyed his Government’s condolence
                            on the death of Mr. Whitelaw Reid. Please express this Government’s
                            sincere appreciation of this sympathy and of the high tribute paid to
                            the qualities which enabled Mr. Reid to maintain between Great Britain
                            and the United States a cordial bond of friendship.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Knox.</hi>s</signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>